The paper deals with the evaluation of saliency maps, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning applications, particularly in image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the fidelity of saliency maps, which is a measure of how well they capture the true relevance of pixels to the classifier output. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the reliability and consistency of saliency metrics, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
